description:
Unit 44 is a four-issue sci-fi/comedy miniseries published March - June 2015 by Alterna Comics as a digital-first initiative to ComiXology.

Wes Locher provided both the story and letters and the illustrations and colors were completed by Eduardo Jimenez.

Collected in Unit 44.
name: Unit 44

description:
Five issue mini-series.

The story is about two adolescents: Madison, one of the hottest chicks in school and former girlfriend of one of the football players, and Duncan, a nerd nobody wants to hang out with and who likes to listen to punk rock music. Somehow, the two become friends and soon thereafter they already have to leave town.

All chapter titles are named after classic punk rock songs (that also appear on the mix-tape "Call-to-Arms" that Duncan gives to Madison in the first issue):

  • #1 - "What We Do Is Secret" by Germs
  • #2 - "That’s When I Reach For My Revolver" by Mission Burma
  • #3 - "Bigmouth Strikes Again" by The Smiths
  • #4 - "Help Save the Youth of America" by Billy Bragg
  • #5 - "Death or Glory" by The Clash

Collected in We Can Never Go Home.
name: We Can Never Go Home

description:
English digital chapters.

Somewhere in post WWII Central Europe exists an orphanage where children having survived a mysterious, transformative virus are admitted. Czechoslovakia, 1949. What Evil lurks within the walls of an ancient children's infirmary? After the brutal murder of her parents, Sarah, a young orphan, is about to discover that and much more. From long-buried secrets to imminent battles, the fate of man, and monster, lie with young Sarah. A gothic tale of horror from David Muñoz (co-writer of Guillermo Del Toro's The Devil's Backbone film) and artist Tirso.
name: Whispers in the Walls
